<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="40" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1520,2013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1736,1761]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Remarks.</emphasis>
The test of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[458,604,1736,1761]" class="Echinoidea" family="Diadematidae" genus="Echinothrix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diadematoida" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="calamaris">
<emphasis box="[458,604,1736,1761]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">E. calamaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[1004,1134,1736,1761]" class="Echinoidea" family="Diadematidae" genus="Echinothrix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diadematoida" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="diadema">
<emphasis box="[1004,1021,1737,1760]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1037,1134,1736,1761]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">diadema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having naked adapical medial zones in the interambulacra, conspicuously inflated aboral ambulacra, no enlarged ambulacral tubercles at the ambitus and small auricles with low connecting ridges in the interambulacra. In life, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[1185,1332,1808,1833]" class="Echinoidea" family="Diadematidae" genus="Echinothrix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diadematoida" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="calamaris">
<emphasis box="[1185,1332,1808,1833]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">E. calamaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[369,498,1844,1869]" class="Echinoidea" family="Diadematidae" genus="Echinothrix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diadematoida" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="diadema">
<emphasis box="[369,498,1844,1869]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">E. diadema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having banded, usually pale or white primary spines, and concentrations of gold or light brown, poison-gland bearing spines in the ambulacra that are much shorter and more sharply pointed than the interambulacral primaries. See 
<bibRefCitation author="Coppard, S. E. &amp; Campbell, A. C." box="[558,893,1916,1941]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" pagination="93 - 112" refId="ref9362" refString="Coppard, S. E. &amp; Campbell, A. C. (2006) Taxonomic significance of test morphology in the echinoid genera Diadema Gray, 1825 and Echinothrix Peters, 1853 (Echinodermata). Zoosystema, 28 (1), 93 - 112." type="journal article" year="2006">Coppard &amp; Campbell (2006)</bibRefCitation>
for an in-depth discussion of the test features distinguishing the two species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1520,2013]" box="[199,1437,1988,2013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">
This species was recently added to the 
<collectingRegion box="[633,666,1988,2013]" country="United Kingdom" name="Surrey" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Sri</collectingRegion>
Lankan echinoid faunal list by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jayakody, S." box="[1018,1209,1988,2013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" pagination="370 - 372" refId="ref9922" refString="Jayakody, S. (2012) Provisional checklist of sea urchins (Echinodermata: Echinoidea) of Sri Lanka. In: Weerakoon, D. K. &amp; Wijesundara, S. (Eds.), The National Red List 2012 of Sri Lanka; Conservation Status of the Fauna and Flora. Ministry of Environment, Colombo, Sri Lanka, pp. 370 - 372." type="book chapter" year="2012">Jayakody (2012)</bibRefCitation>
. Our study confirms
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="40">
the presence of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[340,488,151,176]" class="Echinoidea" family="Diadematidae" genus="Echinothrix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diadematoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="40" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="calamaris">
<emphasis box="[340,488,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="40">E. calamaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[532,650,151,176]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="5" pageNumber="40">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[664,812,151,176]" class="Echinoidea" family="Diadematidae" genus="Echinothrix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diadematoida" pageId="5" pageNumber="40" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="calamaris">
<emphasis box="[664,812,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="40">E. calamaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed from the western Indian Ocean (
<bibRefCitation author="Samyn, Y." box="[158,303,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="40" pagination="193 - 212" refId="ref10845" refString="Samyn, Y. (2003) Shallow-water regular echinoids (Echinodermata: Echinoidea) from Kenya. African Zoology, 38, 193 - 212." type="journal article" year="2003">Samyn 2003</bibRefCitation>
) to the eastern Indian Ocean (
<bibRefCitation author="Putchakarn, S. &amp; Sonchaeng, P." box="[640,993,188,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="40" pagination="417 - 428" refId="ref10801" refString="Putchakarn, S. &amp; Sonchaeng, P. (2004) Echinoderm fauna of Thailand: History and inventory reviews. Science Asia, 30, 417 - 428. https: // doi. org / 10.2306 / scienceasia 1513 - 1874.2004.30.417" type="journal article" year="2004">Putchakarn &amp; Sonchaeng 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sastry, D. R. K." box="[1005,1140,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="40" pagination="1 - 387" refId="ref11009" refString="Sastry, D. R. K. (2007) Echinodermata of India, an annotated list. Records of the Zoological Survey of India. Occasional Paper, 271, 1 - 387." type="journal article" year="2007">Sastry 2007</bibRefCitation>
) and beyond (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark, A. M. G. &amp; Rowe, F. W. E." pageId="5" pageNumber="40" refId="ref9175" refString="Clark, A. M. G. &amp; Rowe, F. W. E. (1971) Monograph of Shallow-water Indo-West Pacific Echinoderms. British Museum Natural History Publications, London, 238 pp." type="book" year="1971">Clark &amp; Rowe 1971</bibRefCitation>
for a summary).
</paragraph>
